race.comment: PRESIDENT ROLEX (3) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 1.3 lengths from the winner Tarawi Mike in third(22.81) at Maitland. Rates highly and will give a great sight. TEN BOB NOTE (8) was sent out long odds last time but charged out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 3.5 lengths fifth (22.70) over 400m at Maitland. Worth another chance. FOOLS RUSH IN (1) filled the minor placings three races on end before breaking through for a maiden win last time, scoring by a nose (23.18) at this track. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Can measure up again. SOFT WHISPER (6) cannot be ruled out.
